modules.description: Provides a way to convert values wrapped in a container type to S-expressions, using a custom function for the inner value. Works with a parameterized type that holds a single value of any type. Used to serialize structured data in a format suitable for parsing and debugging.

Controls the order in which nodes are processed as starting points in graph traversal, prioritizing nodes with completed traversals. Operates on graph node identifiers and traversal state records. Used to optimize search paths in dependency resolution and graph analysis workflows.

Converts values of type t to S-expression format using the sexp_of_t function. Works with the t type, which represents structured data elements. Used to serialize custom data types for debugging or configuration purposes.

Provides functions to perform topological sorting on directed acyclic graphs (DAGs), including a Kahn's algorithm implementation and a depth-first search-based method. Operates on graph representations using adjacency lists and node sets. Used to determine processing order for tasks with dependencies, such as build systems or workflow pipelines.

Provides operations to compare, hash, and serialize topological orderings as S-expressions. Works with the `t` type, representing ordered lists of nodes in a directed acyclic graph. Used to ensure consistent representation and storage of graph traversal results in persistent data structures.
